Following several confirmed cases cholera, Hong Kong health officials have been on guard.  The Department of Health reminded the public to be aware of the disease and some preventative measures, stressing that to "prevent cholera and other food-borne diseases, members of the public should observe good personal and food hygiene at all times."
 The Department of Health is reminding the public to maintain good personal and food hygiene as new cholera cases are reported. 

In the kitchen, handwashing, thorough cooking, and proper storage are essential.  The confirmed cholera cases in Hong Kong involved inadequately heated food, especially shellfish.  The Department of Health will regularly inspect restaurants.
 After the outbreak of several isolated cholera cases, the Department of Health (DH) issued warnings to the public to be on guard against the food-borne disease.

The DH issued a list of suggestions for the prevention of cholera and other gastro-intestinal diseases. Most of the list involved practicing good hygiene.


